\section{\ecac{} Model}
\label{sec:model-paperC}

\ecac{} is an Eventually Consistent Access Control model designed for offline-first operation with rigorous security and auditability. This section presents the conceptual model and its formal guarantees.

\ecac{} combines four key elements: (1)~a causal event log with deterministic deny-wins replay, (2)~verifiable credentials for time-bounded authorization epochs, (3)~a hybrid ABAC/RBAC policy model with deny-overrides semantics, and (4)~per-tag encryption with key rotation.

We outline formal guarantees for convergence, safety, determinism, audit integrity, and leaver security (post-revocation confidentiality under key rotation). The system's four-phase lifecycle (Ingest, Validate, Replay, Query) is summarized in Figure~\ref{fig:ecac-overview-paperC}. The remainder of this section expands each phase and uses subsequent figures to clarify how the causal event log, in-band trust, deny-wins gating, and (optional) confidentiality interact to produce a deterministic authorization outcome.

