The event DAG acts as a convergent CRDT: merging logs from partitions is a set union of nodes and edges---commutative, associative, and idempotent---ensuring eventual consistency.

Operation structure and DAG mechanics are detailed in Figure~\ref{fig:dag-structure-paperC}. Each operation carries a signed header with parent links, HLC timestamp, producer key, and typed payload. The activated/pending staging is what makes out-of-order ingestion safe: replicas can accept events opportunistically, but only replay events once their causal predecessors are present, ensuring that every replica topologically sorts the same complete DAG prefix.

