\subsection{Multi-Node Sync Convergence (E12)}

\textbf{Method.} We evaluate convergence using an in-process deterministic simulation with three nodes to isolate protocol behavior from network variability. Each node maintains an independent DAG and exchanges operations via simulated gossip (CBOR-serialized ops sent between in-memory DAGs).

\textbf{Scenario 1: No partition.} Three nodes each generate 1,000 operations independently (3,000 total), then sync all ops. After sync, all three produce the same replay digest.

\textbf{Scenario 2: Partition + heal with REVOKE.} Three nodes share an initial 600 ops (200 per writer). Node~C is partitioned from \{A,B\}. Both sides continue writing; node~A issues a REVOKE targeting C's key during the partition. After healing and full sync, all three nodes converge to the same digest, confirming that C's post-revoke effects are deterministically skipped.

